item.content:encoded:
Say what you mean. They'll get over it!

THE WAR OVER THE RIGHTS TO THE RAINBOW

A Platform For People That Understand Our Right to Free Speech.

I think somewhere along the line and I would really like to know where but we as Americans forgot what our rights as Americans actually are.

That, or we just stopped fighting for those rights that matter most and directed attention elsewhere instead.

But in that time the masses have grown-up to an embarrassing level ignorance !

And I don’t think that the group of people that should be looked at as the problem is at all the ones that are being looked at.
And the only ones keep in mind ,that seem to be pointing fingers on top of trying to blame their inability to accept themselves on the ones who are comfortable in their own skin. Or , god forbid makes them realize just how much they themselves aren’t.

I think this leads to insecurities so it’s easier to place blame rather than man up.

This is a disgrace to me!

It is a disgrace and should be a disgrace to all Of us who are human . And remember what it means to be human .

I hope that these individuals realize is that they are not talked about Or looked at , at all in a way they don’t portray themselves to be. And no more than you or I or anybody else is for that matter .
I don’t care if you’re gay. I don’t care if you’re straight. Or if you’re black. If you’re white. I don’t care if you’re Jewish or Catholic ! I may feel sorry for you but I don’t care what you are! It’s not going to make me dislike you or stop liking you !

What will make me stop liking and defending your decisions is your inability to be able to accept them yourself as well as accept the fact that “not everybody is going to like you.”

Unless you were born under a rock you know what society was raised like. Therefore, you should be ready , able and willing to take on the responsibility that comes along with leading such controversial lifestyle. ( when I say controversial lifestyle I am speaking universally not about a particular lifestyle its meant to represent anything recognized as being different)

It’s no different than me choosing to voice my opinion always. And always being prepared to take a hit or at least defend myself against one because of it. But you don’t hear me crying about how the masses dislike honesty. That’s just not how it works. You continue to do what you do until society finally decides to mind their own fucking business like he rest of us Red blooded open minded Americans!

You can’t expect to be treated like everybody else but not willing to conform even a little in order to do so. NEWS FLASH! Everyone has to conform a little , it doesn’t matter who you are , or what you believe in! That’s just what we have to do in order to gain any kind of footing in this country , unfortunately.

But I’m sorry I’m over it. I shouldn’t have to watch what I say and tiptoe around what I say because so-and-so could get offended. And if I do , then I think so-and-so should have to educate themselves enough to where they no longer get offended . And are able to laugh at themselves or see exactly how stupid they look to the rest of the world and why whatever was said to offend them was said to begin with!

I am an honest person . I’m not a mean person ,however I can be. But I don’t say anything that I am not able to defend or that I am not prepared to be punched in the face for, like I stated earlier. I feel if you are going to cry about who you are then maybe you are the one who doesn’t like who you are. Did you ever think of that? That’s probably not the case I’m sure, but, If you love and believe in who you are and what you stand for, than maybe you should learn how to fight! Legit! You’re giving your entire , whatever group of people , a bad name and you’re making the rest of us come across as a bunch of tissue paper soft push overs and I don’t like that.

I am considered legally to be a midget (did you smirk a little? It’s ok, I did too 😂) I also have a history of mental illness. Coupled with a short bullshit tolerance and BAM! Branded for life , regardless of the reality of my mental status today as opposed to the one I just mentioned having been a more past tense concern. However, I am still considered to be disabled. So….come at me because nobody has any worry or second thought about coming up to me and reminding me how short I am , But not in so many nice words. And they definitely aren’t concerned with my feelings when it is brought to my attention that I’m crazy. Do I cry about it ? Maybe . (I am human after all.)One thing is for sure, I certainly won’t in front of whoever has caused the discomfort. I’ve never once thought to run And tell.
That’s an option?

See, that’s what irritates me . Even though all of this is going on in the world with this “oh that hurt my feelings” and racism accusations tossed in somewhere with demanding respect while throwing a stolen tv through a stores front window in an attempt to prove your life matters.

Get real, all of this does nothing except help the idiots that have made y’all feel it was necessary to “protest” , prove that you do not deserve any kind of respect and maybe it’s that behavior and not your private life choices or your skin color , thats making you look bad.

Yet, anybody can come at me ?! And I’m a total lunatic mega bitch if I god forbid, treat whoever accordingly!? That’s some straight Bull shit right there! Nobody is ever sensitive to me or my feelings and don’t think twice. And they should because what if I finally had enough and went all “ Me, Myself and Irene” on their asses? I mean, why not, I am a crazy dwarf after all!
LOL . I even laughed at myself just now while envisioning this) Why because it’s true. I can’t get mad at someone to the point of making a big deal when it’s something that, although worded ignorantly, is true.
I can laugh at their stupidity though. And I can’t respect someone , and I don’t care what color you are or who you like to sleep with , who can’t show respect towards me as well! And I don’t feel that I should have to. I don’t feel that anyone should have to. I don’t feel I should have to watch my mouth . I don’t feel I should have to speak politically correct . I feel like I should be me and that should be good enough. I don’t care what happened to your ancestors or mine. I care what is happening to me and mine now.

So unless I am hoarding a colony of all races and religions somewhere where they cannot escape and they are sewing all of my little midget pants and making all of my customized little dwarf furniture against their will, then I have no reason to take the blame and you have no right to be mad for what was done when neither of us even existed.

If we did then the world should hate God. ( insert long exaggerated “GASP” from the masses here) And with that being said ……

…..welcome to Bunk and Hacker! Where you can say how you really feel but you better mean and stand behind what you’re really saying. Remember you are not the only one who has a right to speak. So listen and read at your own risk! NOTE: that we are not responsible for your weak mind. So if you end up looking over the side of a bridge and or with zero self-esteem left as a result , it isn’t our problem . You were warned. For the rest of you.

Your welcome.

Stay tuned…

item.content:encoded:
Healing Through the Altered States of Consciousness

Kimbralee Garcia

Post University

Table of Contents

Hypnosis - The Space Between;

Healing Through the Altered States of Consciousness

Abstract

Hyp-"notes"…………………………………………………………………………………..5

Life is but a dream……………………………………………………………………………6

Hypnagogic Hallucinations………………………………………………………………….7

The Reason…………………………………………………………………………………….7

Healing through trance………..………………………………………………………………8

References………..………………………………………………………10

Abstract

Something that has been said about Hypnosis that I particularly liked was part of A quote which I've cited partially here, stating,

"one persistent barrier to the scientific use of hypnosis has been the idea that it involves a special and "mysterious" state of consciousness, often referred to as a trance." The state of trance has also been compared to that of meditation states of consciousness. And because the hypnotic brain serves to tap neurocognitive questions and our cognitive assays allow new light showing more neutral bases of Hypnosis. This has been referred to this as "crosstalk." And should enhance research and provide more insight into the neural mechanisms of the meditation green. Because Hypnosis and meditation also represent two important historical influential landmarks of western and eastern civilization. The combination of the ancient Eastern meditation techniques and today's Western Clinical Hypnosis gives hope to each of them, being of some asset to the other in terms of enrichment. And the possibility of enlightenment.

Keywords: Hypnosis, altered states of consciousness, awareness, hypnogia, meditation,

Hypnosis - The Space Between;

Healing Through the Altered States of Consciousness

Hyp-" notes"

Hypnosis in some way, shape, or form has been in all areas of the world and is as old as time. For years, Hypnosis has been more known to be used in things like regression therapy.

James Braid developed the word hypnosis. He Defined Hypnosis as a state of focused attention. And also set the eye fixation technique to induce the hypnotic state. Noticeably, Hypnosis is similar to various forms of meditation in psychological and physiological aspects. There have been several benefits to Hypnosis, especially in treatments For things like anxiety, PTSD, trauma, and even pain management. And in something like addiction, all have been known to be seemingly "cured" after a patient goes through hypnotherapy. It seems As though it has been plagued with the accusations that Hypnosis works through brainwashing. Of course, a sort of mind control is at somebody else's hand. Allowing subliminal and deliberate messages and behaviors and or patterns to be instilled into another person's mind without them having any way of knowing or control over what was being "implanted ." This has given reason even for such rumors as possession or that this is some form of dark magic and not something that is to be considered helpful or of the positive use of any kind. Many still believe that it is the "devil's work" that is being done when using hypnotherapy.

Is the suggestion of another the reason for the patient to overcome their anguish? Or is it something different? Something less sinister and yet even more intriguing? Many studies have shown that it has nothing to do with suggestive behaviors or implanted subliminal messages. But instead, a sort of key to a door that unlocks an altered state of consciousness. Or what some have referred to it as altered states of awareness. And that results in the patient's ability to cure themselves.

Life is but a dream

Sadly, Hypnosis seems to alter the brain state to allow external information to dominate over one's internal goals. (2)

A constant uphill battle comes along with hypnotherapy and the mysterious state of consciousness, often referred to as a trance that is induced. Because the hypnotic brain can serve as a way to tap neurocognitive questions, it can also shed new light on the basis for Hypnosis. They called this "crosstalk." (1), And it is thought that it should allow enhancing research towards an increasing body of evidence that provides insight into the neural mechanisms of the meditation brain state as well. The idea is that through Hypnosis, we can walk between spaces of time. Or if you prefer to walk between various stages of consciousness or awareness. Shamans, for instance, believe in something similar, which they refer to as realm walking. It is part of a process they endure to achieve self-awareness. And with that divinity. The divinity that comes with the recognition of oneself and the purpose for their existence.

Hypnagogic Hallucinations.

They are known to occur just before we fall asleep. And can be characterized by what has been described as a slide show like a group of bizarre images, faces, figures, animals, print, writing, even things such as hearing one's name being whispered or music and temporary paralysis noted to be experienced during hypnagogia. (4).

These have been known to cultivate intuition, inspiration, and creative insight for those who experience it. Which, by the way, is roughly 72 to 77% of the population. However, most are not aware of it at all. (4)

The Reason.

It has been shown that Magnetite crystals, found in brain cells along with meninges, are what causes these hallucinations. There are 5 million magnetite crystals per gram in the brain. And 20x that in meninges. (3)

Bio magnetite crystals are oriented in the brain in a particular way that amplifies their magnetic moment. So much so that they can act as a system and work the ability of the brain to sense every feeling, such as feelings of instinct. Furthermore, studies have even shown that the proximity of crystal-containing brain cells connects them to the pituitary and pineal glands. And that this is the reason for the belief that these glands may use information from the earth's magnetic field to regulate the release of hormones inside the brain. This, as a result, gives us the ability to control consciousness and awareness levels. (3)

The Hypnogia imagery shows the existence of various states of consciousness. And also the presence of clairvoyance and telepathy. Other sources, like the one found in the book titled the Hypnogagia-Altered States, (4)

suggest the evolutionary possibility of many realities. And that what we call "wakefulness" is just one of these realities or altered states.

Healing through trance.

So what does this all mean exactly? These findings suggest that acceptance, if nothing else, can be found somewhere between "here" and "there."

Hypnosis and meditation each have various but specific meanings for altered states of consciousness. Some may think of these states of awareness either psychologically or spiritually. This depends probably on which part of the world you're looking at it from. Western medicine obviously and more expectedly thinks of Hypnosis from a more psychological perspective. Hypnosis and meditation are believed to be somewhat of a secondary phenomenon. They both are slightly culturally recognized. Because of this, the way of thought, behavior, and experience is a continuum of consciousness.

Studies have been done on the explanation of psychic abilities and creative intuition that show the possibility that our brain may be able to tap into other states of consciousness at will.

Einstein and Aristotle; both believed and were also known to participate in such practices as Hypnosis and mindful meditation to induce this particular state of awareness. The same form is achieved, mind you, through spiritualism and hallucinogenic drug use. These are all adapted strategies to achieve this level of understanding known as "Hypnagogia ." There seems to be a very distinct common, in particular, to channel into this altered state of consciousness. A disassociative like transcendental altered state allows for the discovery of oneself, and the ability to heal what they believe in has plagued them. All of these practices produce a sort of portal leading directly into the same state of altered consciousness nonetheless. I wonder if the level of intensity that is made to go through to achieve this gift of divinity is part of the journey. It seems that if everyone is led to the same place, the need to go through what can sometimes become fatal practices wouldn't be necessary. And even more, suffering individuals could still experience comfort and relief from hypnotherapy.

My Percieved Discovery of Self Awareness Written solely but based partially off of My Own Experiences & Encounters

Kimbralee D. Garcia – (a thinker of what she thinks is real)

Post University

Although part of an assignment, I have added it to conclude an already in progress both intentionally and sometimes not, written and documented personal researched study theory pertaining to the discovery of Self Awareness. It was written based off of a plethora of written and oral documents used as reference towards this assignment (the summarization) And resulted in a real and documented experience of my own personal epiphany. I have never thought harder to hold onto an actual thought in my life,  than I did while doing this assignment – Kim Garcia

 

 

The Summarization

Most of the way we act is a result of our own individual personality traits. Bio psychologists aren’t so thought provoked but rather try to look at the more scientific reasoning behind a person‘s actions.

  Whereas experimental psychologist’s research is extremely thought-provoking.

 

Such research for this assignment has suggested me to be a liable source. Experimental psychologist branch out beyond monkey see monkey do. They dive further into not only what a person sees and does and into why a person sees the things the way that they do and why a person does.

  Which brings me to my conclusion that none of this “life” I will call it, can at all be real. I believe it’s a state of mind or awareness or just knowing that two can exist. Because we would not exist in the form we perceive ourselves to be in if it wasn’t for the existence of even just one shared perception. In someway shape or form. I believe that it is, and if you knew me the irony of this Epiphany to me anyways, is probably the reasoning for how I am also perceived by myself and others to be. Whether or not we say that we do or not, this shared perception or thought, that there is a “God“ or a “higher power“. A higher entity in some form exists to all of us whether consciously or not. And why it is probably pretty vital to maybe not focus so much in the tech area in life and instead, literally think for a while. Because if not the severity of the effects technology will inevitably have on our personalities is the most unsettling and disturbing thought I care not to have to think about . Let alone experience.

  Only being able to define your personality based off of what you have read, speaking of future and current generations, and only read what you should feel which by the way is another persons perception. And how you should feel would result in a cold and completely synthetic reality. There would eventually be absolutely no actual compassion. I believe it to be compassion that is responsible for us being able to share the perception or idea of faith in every right and definition you believe or understand it to mean. We believe in something is the point. We care to dream.

 

I believe technology will kill the dreamer. And one can interpret that however their brain allows them to in order to accept the fact of the thought existing.

 

  This is why now more than ever maybe, “PsyTech”(Essentials of Understanding Psychology, 14th Edition ; Ch 1 pg .23)

should be less of an “experimental” area of psychology. And maybe the first “shared psychological perceptive” amongst researchers atleast for the time being. Maybe it already is and I am just stumbling upon the results of my own study. Whatever the reasoning may be.

 

  However , pertaining to the generalized areas of psychology, whether “Bio” or Experimental”. There is no point in that circle.

 One wouldn’t exist without the other in either believed sense…..

 

…. And life is but a dream.

 

( I apologize for the overly dramatic “row your boat” addition to the otherwise conclusion of my response to the given assignment. However I found it suitable and made the above written translation seem a little lighthearted and easier to choke down)
